CeCe was one of Bruno Tonioli's panelists on BBC One's DanceX. CeCe made a guest appearance on ITV's Dancing on Ice in early 2009, where she was seen helping one of the groups that were selected to skate and sing at the same time.
In 2010, CeCe Sammy founded an artist development and music management company with legendary artist manager Frank DiLeo.
In 2014 and 2015, CeCe Sammy appeared as head vocal coach and judge on the second and third seasons of Endemol's Your Face Sounds Familiar Georgia.
She once again reprised the role as vocal judge for a select number of episodes during the fourth season which started in May 2015.
In 2015, CeCe Sammy worked as a vocal coach on new ITV series Get Your Act Together.

In 2017, CeCe Sammy worked with manufacturer VTech to launch the Kidi Super Star, a karaoke microphone and stand which reduces the vocals on any song.
In 2019, BBC launched "Bring The Noise" campaign and CeCe was a BBC Ambassador and gave her top tips for teaching singing to primary school children and teachers.
In 2018, CeCe Sammy launched a new music therapy initiative called ‘The Power of Muzik’, which empowers and inspires young people going through hard times.
As part of the initiative, CeCe Sammy formed a collective of singers who have performed at top UK music events throughout 2018.
CeCe's released a debut book called "If You Can Speak You Can Sing" was released in February 2019.
